User Role: <{ switch( $role ) }>
    <{ case( 'admin' ) }>
        Administrator - Full Access
    <{ case( 'moderator' ) }>
        Moderator - Limited Access
    <{ case( 'user' ) }>
        Regular User - Basic Access
    <{ default }>
        Guest - No Access
<{ endswitch }>

Priority Level: <{ switch( $priority ) }>
    <{ case( 1 ) }>
        Critical
    <{ case( 2 ) }>
        High
    <{ case( 3 ) }>
        Medium
    <{ case( 4 ) }>
        Low
    <{ default }>
        Unknown Priority
<{ endswitch }>

Feature Status: <{ switch( $enabled ) }>
    <{ case( true ) }>
        Enabled
    <{ case( false ) }>
        Disabled
<{ endswitch }>

Nested Example:
<{ switch( $category ) }>
    <{ case( 'tech' ) }>
        Technology Category
        <{ switch( $subcategory ) }>
            <{ case( 'software' ) }>
                - Software Development
            <{ case( 'hardware' ) }>
                - Hardware Engineering
            <{ default }>
                - General Technology
        <{ endswitch }>
    <{ case( 'business' ) }>
        Business Category
        <{ switch( $subcategory ) }>
            <{ case( 'finance' ) }>
                - Financial Services
            <{ case( 'marketing' ) }>
                - Marketing & Sales
            <{ default }>
                - General Business
        <{ endswitch }>
    <{ default }>
        Other Category
<{ endswitch }>

Variable Case Example: <{ switch( $userType ) }>
    <{ case( $adminType ) }>
        Admin User Type
    <{ case( $guestType ) }>
        Guest User Type
    <{ default }>
        Unknown User Type
<{ endswitch }>